==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin [[statua]] (statue), derived from Latin [[statuere]] (to set up or erect), derived from Latin [[status]] (position).
===Noun===
'''statue'''
#A three-dimension work of art, usually of a person or animal, usually created by sculpting, carving, molding, or casting.
===Derived terms===
*[[Statuelike]]
*[[Statuesque]]
